01:21:57.458 --> 01:22:01.250
Twice you were the obscure
object of desire in my books.

01:22:01.917 --> 01:22:04.250
The books failed.
My fault, not yours.

01:22:04.458 --> 01:22:07.458
But I know you
inside out. It's scary.

01:22:07.667 --> 01:22:10.208
Don't be misled.
You didn't make me up.

01:22:10.500 --> 01:22:13.042
I'm telling that whatever
restlessness you've felt...

01:22:13.333 --> 01:22:16.292
whatever moodiness
and unpredictability...

01:22:16.542 --> 01:22:18.833
you've broken
hearts with...

01:22:19.625 --> 01:22:21.958
and baby, you're
a heartbreaker...

01:22:23.458 --> 01:22:25.625
it's all over
tonight.

01:22:27.708 --> 01:22:31.333
Where'd you get that confidence?
Or are you scared?

01:22:32.000 --> 01:22:33.250
I'm not David.

01:22:33.625 --> 01:22:36.500
I created you twice out
of my imagination.

01:22:36.750 --> 01:22:39.875
I wrote about you before
I even knew you existed.

01:22:40.083 --> 01:22:42.917
Except one day,
I knew I'd meet you.

01:22:44.542 --> 01:22:45.958
Well, what am I thinking?

01:22:46.167 --> 01:22:48.875
You're thinking, "I wish
he'd shut up and kiss me."

01:22:50.750 --> 01:22:53.250
- But you're late.
- I'm not late.

01:22:53.625 --> 01:22:55.625
I think I'm right
on time for you.

01:22:56.125 --> 01:22:59.833
But why would I kiss you here with
your apartment two blocks away?

01:23:00.083 --> 01:23:02.583
- How did you know?
- Why wouldn't I know?

01:23:02.792 --> 01:23:05.250
You were "Steffi"
in my first book...

01:23:05.458 --> 01:23:07.417
and "Louise" in my second...

01:23:11.625 --> 01:23:13.083
and now you're Nola.

01:23:41.750 --> 01:23:43.250
- Hello?
- Movers.

01:23:43.458 --> 01:23:46.833
Come right up, please.
I'll leave the door open.

01:24:01.208 --> 01:24:02.333
Wake up!

01:24:05.167 --> 01:24:07.417
The movers are here
with my things.

01:24:07.667 --> 01:24:09.542
Sorry about last night.

01:24:09.917 --> 01:24:13.333
The second you left for
the drugstore I conked out.

01:24:13.625 --> 01:24:16.208
You must've been so disappointed
when you got back.

01:24:16.542 --> 01:24:19.375
- The moving men are here?
- Yup. It's 7:30.

01:24:19.667 --> 01:24:22.125
- Listen, Bonnie.
- I made some coffee.

01:24:22.417 --> 01:24:24.875
- Bonnie, listen.
- What is it?

01:24:25.125 --> 01:24:26.292
I have to...

01:24:26.958 --> 01:24:28.417
talk to you.

01:24:28.667 --> 01:24:30.375
All right, I'm listening.

01:24:30.625 --> 01:24:32.833
You got to listen.

01:24:33.083 --> 01:24:36.875
- I've done a terrible thing.
- I bet it's a really bad thing.

01:24:37.125 --> 01:24:39.708
- No, you should listen.
- All right.

01:24:40.792 --> 01:24:43.250
I don't know how to say it, but...

01:24:44.833 --> 01:24:48.625
- I wanna call this off.
- What are you talking about?

01:24:49.375 --> 01:24:51.208
I know you'll think I'm the most...

01:24:51.458 --> 01:24:54.167
fucked-up son of a bitch in
the world, and I am.

01:24:54.417 --> 01:24:57.625
I'll try and be honest in
my own stupid way.

01:24:58.292 --> 01:25:00.167
I met someone else, Bonnie.

01:25:02.125 --> 01:25:03.542
You what?

01:25:04.208 --> 01:25:06.500
Listen, I met someone else.

01:25:07.667 --> 01:25:11.083
I met someone else. I don't
know how else to say it.

01:25:11.542 --> 01:25:14.625
- How could you?
- You have every right to hate me.

01:25:15.708 --> 01:25:19.375
- I just moved in yesterday.
- I'm just so screwed up.

01:25:19.667 --> 01:25:21.500
I wish I could put
it another way, but...

01:25:21.708 --> 01:25:23.542
I can't believe what I'm hearing.

01:25:23.792 --> 01:25:27.083
- Moving in together...
- Yeah, it was your idea!

01:25:27.333 --> 01:25:29.083
I know, and if I could explain it...

01:25:29.375 --> 01:25:31.750
So when did you meet
this "someone else"?

01:25:32.125 --> 01:25:34.500
- That's not important...
- No, it is!

01:25:34.708 --> 01:25:36.333
I have rearranged my goddam life!

01:25:36.542 --> 01:25:39.125
I know you did. And
this is so difficult to...

01:25:39.375 --> 01:25:42.417
- You said you loved me!
- I said I thought I did.

01:25:42.792 --> 01:25:44.875
And believe me, I wanted to.

01:25:45.125 --> 01:25:47.542
- You're a wonderful person.
- Know what?

01:25:47.833 --> 01:25:50.083
- You're a sick son of a bitch.
- You're right.

01:25:50.292 --> 01:25:53.417
- That goes downstairs.
- Get the fuck out, please? Thanks.

01:25:53.708 --> 01:25:56.333
Listen, I accept
full responsibility.

01:25:56.583 --> 01:25:58.250
I'm a total asshole.

01:25:58.542 --> 01:26:00.750
Yeah, you're a total asshole!

01:26:00.958 --> 01:26:04.000
But I thought if I was honest
and brought it up openly...

01:26:04.250 --> 01:26:06.708
that we could understand
that at least...

01:26:07.000 --> 01:26:09.625
I truly do not mean
you any harm.

01:26:09.875 --> 01:26:13.708
I know how you
feel and I feel so bad.

01:26:14.333 --> 01:26:16.917
But if we just
accept me as sick...

01:26:17.125 --> 01:26:20.167
and try to, I know it's
hard, remain rational...

01:26:20.417 --> 01:26:23.500
then we can do this with
the minimum of disruption.

01:26:23.792 --> 01:26:27.708
Naturally, you can store your
stuff here for a while and...

01:26:28.125 --> 01:26:29.625
You're fucking psychotic!

01:26:29.833 --> 01:26:33.083
Bonnie, this is hard and I
just don't know. I'm so...

01:26:33.333 --> 01:26:34.500
Ah, boy!

01:26:37.458 --> 01:26:39.458
What are you doing with my novel?

01:26:41.792 --> 01:26:44.000
Now, that's an only copy!

01:26:50.917 --> 01:26:52.000
Hey, buddy!

01:26:52.292 --> 01:26:55.667
Did you see a woman come
out of here with a manuscript?

01:26:56.375 --> 01:26:58.875
I saw a girl come out the door.

01:26:59.083 --> 01:27:00.500
Where'd she go?

01:27:00.750 --> 01:27:02.833
Tall girl?
Ran across the street.

01:27:57.167 --> 01:27:58.250
In 5...

01:27:58.333 --> 01:27:59.208
4...

01:27:59.417 --> 01:28:00.333
3...

01:28:02.333 --> 01:28:05.167
Now "Manhattan Moods"
goes live to our feature...

01:28:05.375 --> 01:28:07.083
"Luncheon at Le Bijou."

01:28:08.750 --> 01:28:12.792
Hi, I'm Robin Simon.
Welcome to Le Bijou...

01:28:13.042 --> 01:28:15.333
New York's most
exciting restaurant...

01:28:15.542 --> 01:28:18.125
where every day is a
potpourri of the city's...

01:28:18.333 --> 01:28:21.958
most rich and
famous residents.

01:28:22.208 --> 01:28:25.167
I'm sitting here
talking to Evelyn Isaacs...

01:28:25.375 --> 01:28:28.083
Manhattan's most exclusive
real estate broker.

01:28:28.292 --> 01:28:29.875
The woman who has situated...

01:28:30.083 --> 01:28:32.292
- Is that correct?
- I like it.

01:28:32.500 --> 01:28:35.875
The cream of the city's
most luminous residents.

01:28:36.083 --> 01:28:39.458
You were saying you couldn't
get rock star Ennis Taylor...

01:28:39.667 --> 01:28:41.417
into the apartment
he wanted.

01:28:41.625 --> 01:28:45.292
The tenants didn't want the press
and groupies hanging around.

01:28:45.667 --> 01:28:47.917
Must've been leery of wild parties.

01:28:48.167 --> 01:28:51.542
Yes, but Ennis is not what
you'd think from his band.

01:28:51.792 --> 01:28:55.792
He's not violent or destructive,
he's intellectual and sweet.

01:28:56.125 --> 01:28:59.542
But the board of the co-op
had a problem with his snakes.

01:28:59.792 --> 01:29:03.292
They had a problem with
the boa constrictor.

01:29:03.625 --> 01:29:05.333
Any other big name turndowns?

01:29:05.542 --> 01:29:08.583
No, but I got a beautiful triplex
for the Charles Aranows,

01:29:08.792 --> 01:29:12.458
12 rooms on Park Avenue, and they
made one into a Hamptons room.

01:29:12.708 --> 01:29:16.583
Tons of sand from Amagansett
to cover the floor. It's fun!

01:29:17.042 --> 01:29:18.833
Well, thank you. I see.

01:29:19.583 --> 01:29:21.083
It's time to table-hop...

01:29:21.333 --> 01:29:23.958
so we can meet some of
the other exciting patrons...

01:29:24.167 --> 01:29:26.708
who lunch typically at
Le Bijou.

01:29:27.125 --> 01:29:29.958
Look who's here. Senator Bob
Paley! How are you?

01:29:30.208 --> 01:29:32.417
We're here for the celebrity
golf tournament.

01:29:32.625 --> 01:29:34.750
I play every year and
it's a good cause...

01:29:34.958 --> 01:29:36.917
earning money for
the Heart Foundation.

01:29:37.125 --> 01:29:39.208
They say I'll be paired
with Greg Norman.

01:29:39.417 --> 01:29:40.750
Wonderful!

01:29:41.000 --> 01:29:43.958
Any comments about
the recent allegations?

01:29:44.167 --> 01:29:48.000
I think when the facts are in, the
Justice Department will find...

01:29:48.208 --> 01:29:52.000
I made an error of judgement,
without real intent of treason.

01:29:52.208 --> 01:29:53.500
Moving right along...

01:29:53.750 --> 01:29:57.333
I see Dee Bartholemew,
"Empress of Gossip".

01:29:57.625 --> 01:30:02.292
Robin, hi. So rainy out today.
Just this gloomy weather.

01:30:02.667 --> 01:30:06.167
But I love your pin.
Is that Georgian?

01:30:06.417 --> 01:30:08.708
Thank you. No,
it's Art Nouveau.

01:30:08.917 --> 01:30:10.458
Where'd you get it?

01:30:10.667 --> 01:30:13.625
My first husband gave me it for
our 15th wedding anniversary.

01:30:13.875 --> 01:30:17.833
When you say "first", do
I sense a second on the way?

01:30:18.417 --> 01:30:21.917
I ran into Tony Gardella
at the Café Carlyle.

01:30:22.208 --> 01:30:26.208
He had a blissed-out look,
like he was in heaven.

01:30:26.667 --> 01:30:30.042
How'd you manage to put
that smile on his face?

01:30:31.625 --> 01:30:33.083
Using my head.

01:30:33.917 --> 01:30:36.875
Any choice items
for our viewers?

01:30:37.250 --> 01:30:40.208
Very prominent
actress/singer...

01:30:40.458 --> 01:30:43.500
has become pregnant on
visiting Buckingham Palace.

01:30:43.750 --> 01:30:45.375
No names, please.

01:30:45.583 --> 01:30:47.083
Well, thank you.

01:30:49.333 --> 01:30:51.583
Look who's here!
Donald Trump.

01:30:51.833 --> 01:30:53.417
What are you working on?

01:30:53.625 --> 01:30:55.917
I'm working on buying
St Patrick's Cathedral...

01:30:56.167 --> 01:30:57.708
doing a little rip-down job...

01:30:57.917 --> 01:31:00.625
and putting up a tall,
beautiful building.

01:31:00.833 --> 01:31:02.333
That's wonderful!

01:31:02.792 --> 01:31:04.333
- You were great!
- Terrible!

01:31:04.542 --> 01:31:07.750
You said you couldn't do it.
And I said, "Yes, you can."

01:31:08.042 --> 01:31:10.167
No actress-turned-
interviewer...

01:31:10.417 --> 01:31:12.625
- could do it as real as you did.
- I was a jerk.

01:31:12.833 --> 01:31:15.042
You're not a jerk.
You were real!

01:31:15.250 --> 01:31:18.708
No-one cares if it's unpolished.
They find it appealing.

01:31:18.917 --> 01:31:20.875
It's your 15 minutes of fame.

01:31:21.125 --> 01:31:22.917
I never believed what
Andy Warhol said...

01:31:23.167 --> 01:31:27.042
that we're all famous for 15
minutes. Nice, but it's not true.

01:31:27.333 --> 01:31:30.833
Almost nobody will ever be
famous for even one minute.

01:31:31.167 --> 01:31:32.708
So enjoy it!

01:31:32.958 --> 01:31:34.875
How did I swing this?

01:31:35.125 --> 01:31:39.458
Last year I was teaching English,
performing a serious function.

01:31:39.708 --> 01:31:42.750
And suddenly, through a
whirlwind series of events...

01:31:43.000 --> 01:31:46.375
I become the sort of woman I've
always hated. But I'm happier.

01:31:47.583 --> 01:31:49.625
You nervous
about Saturday?

01:31:49.875 --> 01:31:50.792
Are you?

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:52.500
I'm counting the seconds.

01:31:56.458 --> 01:31:58.333
My hands are sweating.
I never sweat.

01:31:58.542 --> 01:32:00.792
- Got the ring?
- What am I, a schmuck? Sure!

01:32:01.000 --> 01:32:04.292
Sophisticated. Very
educated. She sure is!

01:32:04.500 --> 01:32:05.458
Oh, picture!

01:32:06.583 --> 01:32:09.917
I like this girl.
I think she's terrific.

01:32:10.375 --> 01:32:13.542
It's ironic.
You go to get face work...

01:32:13.792 --> 01:32:16.125
and you meet a wonderful
guy who changes your life.

01:32:16.333 --> 01:32:18.083
Better than face work.

01:32:18.417 --> 01:32:21.792
- Think this looks okay?
- You look perfect.

01:32:22.125 --> 01:32:23.583
I expected a bigger turnout.

01:32:23.792 --> 01:32:25.750
Ma, they wanted to keep it small.

01:32:26.833 --> 01:32:28.125
Isn't that...?

01:32:28.708 --> 01:32:30.250
Al Swayze, a
friend of Tony's.

01:32:30.458 --> 01:32:32.417
- Yeah, he...
- Does the weather.

01:32:32.833 --> 01:32:35.500
Right, he does the weather
on channel...

01:32:35.792 --> 01:32:37.500
Hello, how'd you do?

01:32:37.750 --> 01:32:39.208
Congratulations.

01:32:39.500 --> 01:32:41.042
Thank you. My daughter, Iris.

01:32:41.333 --> 01:32:44.417
So glad to meet you.
We enjoy your program.

01:32:44.667 --> 01:32:46.083
Really? Nice to meet you too.

01:32:46.375 --> 01:32:48.292
We watch you
give the weather.

01:32:48.542 --> 01:32:50.417
You're usually wrong.

01:32:51.500 --> 01:32:53.167
Occupational hazard, y'know?

01:32:53.375 --> 01:32:56.833
But you're cheerful.
You're all so cheerful.

01:33:38.375 --> 01:33:40.708
I can't find her.
Did you see her?

01:33:41.000 --> 01:33:42.042
Did I...?

01:33:42.792 --> 01:33:45.000
- What happened?
- She's not in the bathroom.

01:33:45.958 --> 01:33:49.042
- You were with her.
- I don't know what happened to her.

01:33:49.333 --> 01:33:50.958
Frankie, come on.

01:33:51.417 --> 01:33:52.250
Relax.

01:33:52.458 --> 01:33:55.083
How can I relax?
She's gotta be here.

01:33:56.792 --> 01:33:59.667
- What's going on?
- It's all right, Ma. Nothing.

01:33:59.917 --> 01:34:01.792
I'm sure it'll all turn out okay.

01:34:02.042 --> 01:34:04.375
She walked out,
alone. 15, 20 minutes ago.

01:34:04.583 --> 01:34:06.083
- Where'd she go?
- I didn't see.

01:34:06.292 --> 01:34:08.458
- You sure she was alone?
- Absolutely.

01:34:08.667 --> 01:34:11.625
Frankie, go up and stall them.
I'm gonna look around.

01:34:11.833 --> 01:34:13.958
- Where?
- I don't know!

01:34:14.208 --> 01:34:17.583
You're out of your mind.
What'll I tell your parents?

01:34:23.250 --> 01:34:26.875
- Everything's fine.
- I hope she's all right.

01:34:27.167 --> 01:34:29.042
- What's going on?
- She's nervous, Ma.

01:34:29.250 --> 01:34:32.208
She needs time
to fix her makeup.

01:34:32.458 --> 01:34:33.708
Should I go help her?

01:34:33.917 --> 01:34:35.792
- Tony's all right?
- Please don't go help her.

01:34:36.083 --> 01:34:38.917
She'll come out.
Iris, just leave her alone.

01:34:39.167 --> 01:34:41.042
She's gathering herself.

01:34:47.917 --> 01:34:50.125
Olga PS YCHIC READER
AND ADVISER

01:34:53.792 --> 01:34:55.583
Want a reading?

01:34:55.792 --> 01:34:57.042
Come on inside.

01:34:57.250 --> 01:34:59.375
- I'll give you a nice reading.
- No, I'm just walking.

01:34:59.583 --> 01:35:01.250
You look like you need a reading.

01:35:01.500 --> 01:35:03.708
- Really?
- Come inside.

01:35:03.917 --> 01:35:06.417
- Come on in.
- I don't believe in psychics.

01:35:06.917 --> 01:35:09.667
You don't have to
for a reading.

01:35:10.542 --> 01:35:12.042
So what do you do?

01:35:12.292 --> 01:35:13.958
I work in television.

01:35:14.667 --> 01:35:16.458
But you used to do something else?

01:35:16.792 --> 01:35:18.792
Yes, I was a teacher.

01:35:20.083 --> 01:35:21.417
I see...

01:35:22.250 --> 01:35:23.667
the name Beowulf.

01:35:23.875 --> 01:35:24.875
Oh my God!

01:35:25.083 --> 01:35:27.167
Chaucer! I
taught Chaucer.

01:35:27.708 --> 01:35:31.417
- Like some tea? Mint tea?
- I would love a drink.

01:35:32.167 --> 01:35:34.750
I got a drink for you.
No problem.

01:35:35.000 --> 01:35:37.375
So you like television better?

01:35:37.750 --> 01:35:41.708
It's interesting to see who we
choose as our celebrities, and why.

01:35:42.542 --> 01:35:44.167
What makes them tick.

01:35:44.375 --> 01:35:47.167
You learn a lot about a society
by who it celebrates.

01:35:47.458 --> 01:35:48.958
- Is this good?
- Yes, please.

01:35:49.208 --> 01:35:52.042
Like, we did this show
on Sunny Von Bulow...

01:35:52.292 --> 01:35:54.042
and she's a coma patient.

01:35:54.292 --> 01:35:56.667
She lies there in a coma...

01:35:56.917 --> 01:35:58.292
but she's a celebrity.

01:35:59.208 --> 01:36:01.375
You were up there with
her. What happened?

01:36:01.583 --> 01:36:03.292
She was okay. A little nervous.

01:36:03.500 --> 01:36:05.583
Listen, I've got
bad news.

01:36:05.792 --> 01:36:06.792
Here he is.

01:36:07.083 --> 01:36:10.667
The wedding's off, so
why don't you all go home?

01:36:11.125 --> 01:36:12.125
Thank you.

01:36:14.000 --> 01:36:15.875
It's not gonna happen, Iris.

01:36:16.292 --> 01:36:19.083
Just go home. Make sure
Mom gets there.

01:36:19.833 --> 01:36:22.208
Are you all right?
Is she hurt?

01:36:22.417 --> 01:36:24.458
No, nothing like that. Just go on.

01:36:24.708 --> 01:36:26.125
- Thanks.
- I'll be home.

01:36:26.333 --> 01:36:28.458
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

01:36:36.083 --> 01:36:37.792
It's all right. Just...

01:36:38.875 --> 01:36:41.292
I'm here to help you.
Whatever.

01:36:51.375 --> 01:36:53.250
You need a change
in your life.

01:36:53.458 --> 01:36:56.417
You must reevaluate the
plans you were contemplating.

01:36:56.625 --> 01:37:00.333
- I see you change your direction.
- I had planned to get married.

01:37:00.667 --> 01:37:02.750
Perhaps it needs more scrutiny
before you decide.

01:37:03.042 --> 01:37:04.208
Really?

01:37:04.458 --> 01:37:06.625
- When was the wedding?
- Today.

01:37:08.042 --> 01:37:10.708
I left him at the church with
his family and friends.

01:37:10.917 --> 01:37:13.125
My God! What have
I done? I don't know!

01:37:13.333 --> 01:37:16.542
If you're not sure you love him,
it's a mistake to go forward.

01:37:16.792 --> 01:37:19.500
- I am sure. He's wonderful.
- So then I don't understand.

01:37:19.750 --> 01:37:22.792
I feel guilty because I've
had such good luck.

01:37:23.042 --> 01:37:24.958
Everyone I know has
so many problems.

01:37:25.250 --> 01:37:29.208
They're lonely, needy. I
have this guy fall in my lap.

01:37:29.917 --> 01:37:31.125
I still don't get it.

01:37:31.333 --> 01:37:34.000
His name's Tony, and
I said, "You're terrific!"

01:37:34.208 --> 01:37:36.000
"When will the other shoe drop?"

01:37:36.458 --> 01:37:40.292
Some bad part of him that'll ruin things.
But there is no bad part.

01:37:40.708 --> 01:37:42.417
- Well, you provided that.
- Me?

01:37:42.625 --> 01:37:45.625
He's a wonderful guy, but
you screwed things up.

01:37:45.833 --> 01:37:46.833
Why?

01:37:47.125 --> 01:37:50.125
You said it yourself.
It's guilt.

01:37:50.375 --> 01:37:52.833
You don't need a fortune
teller. You need a shrink.

01:37:53.042 --> 01:37:55.625
- Me?
- You meet this wonderful guy, okay?

01:37:55.875 --> 01:37:59.042
You can't believe something so wonderful
can happen to you.

01:37:59.333 --> 01:38:01.292
So you ruin it.

01:38:01.542 --> 01:38:04.750
I did a horrible thing.
He'll never forgive me.

01:38:05.083 --> 01:38:06.500
Who could blame him?

01:38:06.750 --> 01:38:09.250
You want your $10 of
psychic prediction?

01:38:09.458 --> 01:38:12.542
He's going to forgive you.
Obviously, he's crazy about you.

01:38:12.792 --> 01:38:16.917
Just because you've acted like a
horse's ass doesn't mean he will.

01:38:17.167 --> 01:38:20.000
So you tell him
everything you told me...

01:38:20.292 --> 01:38:21.792
and then...

01:38:22.042 --> 01:38:23.500
you give him a big kiss.

01:38:35.208 --> 01:38:36.583
We can be seen...

01:38:37.583 --> 01:38:39.083
or don't you care?

01:38:40.542 --> 01:38:41.708
I don't.

01:38:42.292 --> 01:38:44.125
I care about you.

01:38:47.750 --> 01:38:48.625
Perfect.

01:38:49.833 --> 01:38:53.292
Emotionally it's exactly
where you should be.

01:38:54.375 --> 01:38:56.458
I don't feel I'm there at all.

01:38:56.792 --> 01:38:59.208
Trust it. We'll come
back to it tomorrow.

01:38:59.417 --> 01:39:02.250
We'll stop now and
continue from here tomorrow.

01:39:02.500 --> 01:39:06.417
I feel I know where she's coming
from, but she's contradictory.

01:39:08.292 --> 01:39:12.083
Contradiction is good. Just don't
contradict yourself when you act.

01:39:12.458 --> 01:39:15.208
Play one thing
at a time and trust it.

01:39:15.792 --> 01:39:19.667
You have a hold on it.
Just don't look in the mirror.

01:39:20.792 --> 01:39:22.167
Both of you.

01:39:22.375 --> 01:39:24.417
Don't overplay the lust.

01:39:24.667 --> 01:39:27.375
I know. She's a carnivore.

01:39:29.625 --> 01:39:32.667
- Wanna have a drink?
- Yeah, love to.

01:39:33.208 --> 01:39:34.583
We'll talk.

01:39:36.458 --> 01:39:38.083
I just caught the ending.

01:39:38.292 --> 01:39:41.167
Seems like a terrific scene.
It's great work.

01:39:41.500 --> 01:39:44.667
- You didn't say you were coming.
- I was in the neighbourhood.

01:39:44.875 --> 01:39:46.875
Thought I'd stop by to pick you up.

01:39:47.125 --> 01:39:48.667
You know Greg.

01:39:48.917 --> 01:39:51.083
- How you doing?
- Good to see you again.

01:39:51.292 --> 01:39:55.000
- Going to Moran's round the corner.
- Do you wanna have that drink?

01:39:55.250 --> 01:39:59.000
- I thought we'd walk home together.
- I want to talk to Greg.

01:39:59.500 --> 01:40:03.125
- Thought you might want to walk.
- You know I'm in rehearsal!

01:40:03.375 --> 01:40:06.792
I knew you'd be through by 5,
so what's the big deal?

01:40:07.375 --> 01:40:10.958
I'm going to the bar, but
we can talk tomorrow.

01:40:13.000 --> 01:40:15.833
- Don't crowd me! It's annoying.
- I'm not!

01:40:16.042 --> 01:40:18.708
I came to pick you up.
Thought you'd be glad to see me.

01:40:19.000 --> 01:40:20.792
- Things come up!
- Something's very wrong.

01:40:21.000 --> 01:40:22.917
I stop by and it puts
you in a bad mood.

01:40:23.125 --> 01:40:25.917
- It's because you don't trust me.
- Should I?

01:40:26.125 --> 01:40:29.917
- Suspicious, that's your problem.
- You wanna sleep with the director.

01:40:30.583 --> 01:40:34.458
- I'm not in the mood to argue.
- You said you loved me!

01:40:34.917 --> 01:40:36.833
Why do you want me if
you don't trust me?

01:40:37.042 --> 01:40:39.875
How can I? I turn my back
and you're off with someone.

01:40:40.167 --> 01:40:42.875
I already told you, I
don't want to be closed in.

01:40:43.125 --> 01:40:46.292
- So why are you living with me?
- I'm not! I've got an apartment.

01:40:46.542 --> 01:40:49.042
- I just stay over most nights.
- I don't want to crowd you.

01:40:49.250 --> 01:40:53.167
Let me get a drink and
go talk about the play.

01:40:53.375 --> 01:40:56.875
"Fuck off so I can fuck the
director." I understand.

01:40:57.125 --> 01:40:59.875
I am who I am. I told
you that when we met.

01:41:00.125 --> 01:41:02.208
I always hope it'll be
different, but it never is.

01:41:02.500 --> 01:41:05.625
You love me and you'll be hurt
if I give up on you.

01:41:05.833 --> 01:41:07.667
So think about this.

01:41:08.125 --> 01:41:09.708
Just go home.

01:41:10.083 --> 01:41:13.042
We'll just enjoy the
time we have together...

01:41:13.375 --> 01:41:14.958
and not complicate everything.

01:41:15.167 --> 01:41:17.083
Everything doesn't
have to be questioned.

01:41:17.375 --> 01:41:21.042
You're still saying, "Get lost
so I can sleep with the director."

01:41:21.333 --> 01:41:24.458
Anyone would think I was
the whore of TriBeCa.

01:41:25.000 --> 01:41:28.542
So would you be happy if I said
goodbye and never saw you again?

01:41:29.292 --> 01:41:30.958
That wouldn't make me happy.

01:41:31.167 --> 01:41:34.625
We haven't made love
in weeks. What is that?

01:41:34.833 --> 01:41:38.000
Why do you want me, when I
just lie there like a dead fish?

01:41:38.250 --> 01:41:41.167
But you didn't used to.
What happened?

01:41:41.417 --> 01:41:42.333
Nothing.

01:41:42.583 --> 01:41:43.708
It's me, okay.

01:41:44.125 --> 01:41:48.042
It's me. Let's just stay in tonight
and not over-analyse everything?

01:41:51.750 --> 01:41:53.833
What is it with the pills?

01:41:54.083 --> 01:41:56.833
- Diet pills.
- Oh, please!

01:42:04.417 --> 01:42:05.750
I give up.

01:42:08.292 --> 01:42:11.292
So what do you want for dinner?
What should I buy?

01:42:12.667 --> 01:42:13.917
Spaghetti.

01:42:16.958 --> 01:42:19.208
I was going to ask
you to marry me.

01:42:20.250 --> 01:42:21.500
No, penne...

01:42:21.750 --> 01:42:23.458
with marinara.

01:42:34.917 --> 01:42:36.208
Lee, right?

01:42:36.417 --> 01:42:39.708
Phil Datloff. Bonnie brought
you to a party at my apartment.

01:42:40.042 --> 01:42:43.917
Sure I remember you. You were very
kind. I passed out on your carpet.

01:42:44.417 --> 01:42:46.125
- That I remember.
- That's right.

01:42:46.333 --> 01:42:48.833
What happened to the book
you were toying with?

01:42:49.042 --> 01:42:50.250
It just kind of...

01:42:50.458 --> 01:42:51.625
floated away.

01:42:52.000 --> 01:42:54.250
I thought about it the other day.

01:42:54.583 --> 01:42:56.875
A culture that took a wrong
turn somewhere.

01:42:57.083 --> 01:42:59.417
A flawed individual who
can't find himself.

01:42:59.667 --> 01:43:00.875
That was my book.

01:43:01.083 --> 01:43:04.167
Because V.J. Rajnipal,
a great writer...

01:43:04.375 --> 01:43:07.750
just gave us a manuscript
on the same subject.

01:43:08.000 --> 01:43:09.375
Really, the same subject?

01:43:09.625 --> 01:43:12.125
A society where every single
member is famous.

01:43:12.333 --> 01:43:14.542
There are no uncelebrated people.

01:43:14.833 --> 01:43:16.042
Very satirical.

01:43:17.083 --> 01:43:20.333
I'd like to have seen your
take on the same subject.

01:43:20.542 --> 01:43:21.958
He's a great artist.

01:43:22.167 --> 01:43:23.667
I could never...

01:43:25.750 --> 01:43:28.708
- How's Bonnie?
- Fine. Great girl.

01:43:29.375 --> 01:43:31.458
I think she sold
a screenplay.

01:43:34.292 --> 01:43:38.250
We're at the star-spangled
première of "The Liquidator".

01:43:39.583 --> 01:43:43.000
Unfortunately for the beautiful
people, the weather hasn't held up.

01:43:43.250 --> 01:43:46.500
But the show must go on.
Here's producer, Dalton Freed.

01:43:46.750 --> 01:43:50.417
- Can you believe the weather?
- Unbelievable. How you doing?

01:43:51.167 --> 01:43:52.750
Could be better.

01:43:53.042 --> 01:43:55.500
Hasn't kept people away.
Is this your wife?

01:43:55.792 --> 01:43:59.458
This is a young actress you'll
be hearing a lot about.

01:43:59.750 --> 01:44:01.750
My wife, you know,
she's in rehab.

01:44:02.000 --> 01:44:04.708
I've read the reviews.
Very interesting!

01:44:04.917 --> 01:44:07.583
- I never read reviews.
- And your next project?

01:44:07.792 --> 01:44:10.333
"Birth of a Nation", an
all-black version.

01:44:10.542 --> 01:44:11.667
Can't wait.

01:44:11.875 --> 01:44:15.875
Oh my gosh, Erno DeLucca,
who did Nicole Olivier's wigs!

01:44:17.125 --> 01:44:19.250
I also did her werewolf makeup.

01:44:19.500 --> 01:44:21.458
- Werewolf?
- Yes, twice.

01:44:22.000 --> 01:44:24.167
- Good job. Nice to see you.
- Thank you.

01:44:24.417 --> 01:44:28.333
There'll be lots of big celebrities
tonight. I'll keep my eyes peeled.

01:44:29.083 --> 01:44:31.042
Here's the director. How are you?

01:44:31.250 --> 01:44:32.583
What a night!

01:44:32.833 --> 01:44:36.333
Incredible, like a typhoon. Are
you from the weather channel?

01:44:37.292 --> 01:44:41.292
I hear in your film you actually
have a big rain sequence.

01:44:41.500 --> 01:44:45.167
We have amazing effects,
almost like the real thing.

01:44:45.417 --> 01:44:46.833
Actually, they're better.

01:44:47.083 --> 01:44:48.875
Thank you. Enjoy your night.

01:44:49.167 --> 01:44:51.708
We'll be rooting for it.
I'm really excited about it.

01:44:52.167 --> 01:44:53.875
Nicole Oliver! Here she is!

01:44:54.083 --> 01:44:56.708
One of the stars
with her husband.

01:44:56.917 --> 01:44:59.167
You look beautiful. Show us
what you're wearing.

01:44:59.542 --> 01:45:00.792
I'm soaked.

01:45:01.000 --> 01:45:03.583
Unbelievable. You look great.

01:45:04.500 --> 01:45:06.708
The lights, the ambience,
the greasepaint...

01:45:07.000 --> 01:45:09.208
You can't swing a cat
without hitting a celebrity.

01:45:09.500 --> 01:45:12.792
And the rain didn't
seem to deter many people.

01:45:13.125 --> 01:45:15.375
I'm really excited.
The big première!

01:45:15.583 --> 01:45:18.667
Oh my gosh! Robin Simon
from "Manhattan Moods"!

01:45:19.000 --> 01:45:22.875
Congratulations on your show,
your pregnancy, marriage, everything.

01:45:23.208 --> 01:45:24.583
Doesn't she look beautiful?

01:45:24.833 --> 01:45:27.167
Who knew angels flew so low?
Unbelievable.

01:45:27.458 --> 01:45:31.375
Your show's taken off, and I'm
jealous. What about the rain?

01:45:31.958 --> 01:45:33.667
- It's really something.
- It is!

01:45:33.917 --> 01:45:36.542
Listen, have a great time.
You look incredible!

01:45:37.083 --> 01:45:39.208
We got more people coming.

01:45:39.417 --> 01:45:40.542
I see Sandor!

01:45:43.208 --> 01:45:44.958
We feel sorry for him.

01:45:45.958 --> 01:45:47.167
My goodness!

01:45:52.250 --> 01:45:54.542
- What are you doing...?
- Incredible!

01:45:55.000 --> 01:45:58.458
I haven't seen you for...
At the movies again!

01:45:59.417 --> 01:46:01.333
This is my husband, Tony.

01:46:01.583 --> 01:46:05.292
Nice to meet you.
Congratulations on everything.

01:46:05.875 --> 01:46:08.750
- You're transformed!
- Such a surprise.

01:46:09.042 --> 01:46:13.000
- It's not your kind of movie.
- I interviewed Nicole Olivier.

01:46:13.458 --> 01:46:15.375
I read the interview.
It was marvelous.

01:46:16.042 --> 01:46:19.458
Marvelous? Didn't that used to
be your least-favourite word?

01:46:19.667 --> 01:46:21.917
- Stop it!
- Those crossword puzzles.

01:46:22.917 --> 01:46:24.875
- Want some popcorn?
- I'd love some.

01:46:25.167 --> 01:46:27.000
- Want a bag?
- That'd be great.

01:46:27.208 --> 01:46:28.583
I can't believe...

01:46:30.167 --> 01:46:31.958
Have I become insufferable?

01:46:32.208 --> 01:46:35.625
- No, happy, confident and radiant.
- I am happy.

01:46:36.417 --> 01:46:38.917
- Hi, Jack. Good to see you.
- Great article.

01:46:39.125 --> 01:46:41.667
Robin Simon, I'm so excited
to meet you in person.

01:46:41.875 --> 01:46:43.000
Thank you, darling.

01:46:43.250 --> 01:46:45.708
I love your show.
Such a great broadcaster.

01:46:45.958 --> 01:46:46.958
Aren't you sweet!

01:46:47.167 --> 01:46:49.542
- God bless you.
- God bless you.

01:46:49.750 --> 01:46:51.542
You're so radiant.

01:46:52.417 --> 01:46:55.292
- Thank you. It's luck, Lee.
- Really?

01:46:55.542 --> 01:46:59.167
No matter what the shrinks
and self-help books tell you.

01:46:59.542 --> 01:47:01.875
Love is a question of luck.

01:47:08.292 --> 01:47:10.208
I'm glad you were lucky.

01:47:10.500 --> 01:47:11.875
You with anyone?

01:47:12.083 --> 01:47:13.792
Not at the moment.

01:47:14.750 --> 01:47:16.792
- What are you working on?
- Just the same...

01:47:17.083 --> 01:47:18.750
A novel? A screenplay?

01:47:19.708 --> 01:47:23.708
I did a huge interview at the old
actor's home. Very touching.

01:47:24.083 --> 01:47:27.208
My Uncle Willie's there.
He asked about the autograph.

01:47:27.500 --> 01:47:30.958
We did a report from
Charlie Manson's jail cell.

01:47:31.292 --> 01:47:34.917
- So interesting.
- My nephew wanted his autograph.

01:47:35.417 --> 01:47:37.750
- Oh, dear.
- Next time we're in California.

01:47:38.625 --> 01:47:40.250
Here. Here you go.

01:47:40.458 --> 01:47:42.792
Thanks for...
I don't want to hold you up.

01:47:43.000 --> 01:47:45.958
Just, you know, it's really...

01:47:46.583 --> 01:47:49.208
- And very nice to...
- Great to see you, Lee.

01:47:49.417 --> 01:47:53.125
Really great to see you.
Hope you catch a break.

